requisite skill to exercise the responsibilities of the public practice of geology.
The Board shall waive the examination for licensing as a geologist of an
applicant who makes written application to the Board not later than one year
after appointment of the initial Board, and who otherwise meets the
qualification of this Chapter.
(4) Have at least five years of professional geological work which shall include a
minimum of three years of professional geological work under the supervision
