(8) Health care facilities. – Any one or more buildings, structures, additions,
extensions, improvements, or other facilities, whether or not located on the
same site, machinery, equipment, furnishings, or other real or personal
property suitable for health care or medical care. The term includes, without
limitation, any of the following facilities related to health care:
a. General hospitals or specialized hospitals, such as hospitals for chronic
