instrument of conveyance expressly waives the right, as provided in
G.S. 29-30(a)(2a).
b. A right or claim to an equitable distribution with respect to the
property under G.S. 50-20. A right or claim for equitable distribution
shall not be waived or released in the instrument of conveyance.
(5) An absolute divorce of the spouses. An absolute divorce converts property
held as tenants by the entirety to a tenancy in common.
(6) A judgment of forfeiture ordering divestment of an interest in tenancy by the
entirety pursuant to Chapter 75D of the General Statutes. The effect of a
judgment when one spouse is an innocent person as defined in G.S. 75D-5(i)
is governed by G.S. 75D-8(a)."
