statement of account. – A record authenticated signed by a debtor requesting
that the recipient approve or correct a statement indicating what the debtor
believes to be the aggregate amount of unpaid obligations secured by
collateral as of a specified date and reasonably identifying the transaction or
relationship that is the subject of the request.
