Subsection (h); No Duties or Confirmation. – A secured party does not relinquish possession,
even if a delivery under subsection (h) of this section violates the rights of a debtor. A person to
which collateral is delivered under subsection (h) of this section does not owe any duty to the
secured party and is not required to confirm the delivery to another person unless the person
otherwise agrees or law other than this Article otherwise provides."
