SECTION 79. Article 9 of Chapter 25 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
a new section to read:
"§ 25-9-314.1. Perfection by possession and control of chattel paper.
(a) Perfection by Possession and Control. – A secured party may perfect a security
interest in chattel paper by taking possession of each authoritative tangible copy of the record
evidencing the chattel paper and obtaining control of each authoritative electronic copy of the
electronic record evidencing the chattel paper.
(b) Time of Perfection; Continuation of Perfection. – A security interest is perfected
under subsection (a) of this section not earlier than the time the secured party takes possession
and obtains control and remains perfected under subsection (a) of this section only while the
secured party retains possession and control.
(c) Application of G.S. 25-9-313 to Perfection by Possession of Chattel Paper. –
G.S. 25-9-313(c) and (f) through (i) apply to perfection by possession of an authoritative tangible
copy of a record evidencing chattel paper."
