interest or other lien an authenticated a signed demand for proceeds
before distribution of the proceeds is completed; andcompleted.
b. In a case in which a consignor has an interest in the collateral, the
subordinate security interest or other lien is senior to the interest of the
consignor; andconsignor.
(4) A secured party that is a consignor of the collateral if the secured party
receives from the consignor an authenticated a signed demand for proceeds
before distribution of the proceeds is completed.
(b) Proof of subordinate interest. – Subordinate Interest. – If requested by a secured party,
a holder of a subordinate security interest or other lien shall furnish reasonable proof of the
interest or lien within a reasonable time. Unless the holder does so, the secured party need not
comply with the holder's demand under subdivision (a)(3) of this section.
(c) Application of noncash proceeds. – Noncash Proceeds. – A secured party need not
apply or pay over for application noncash proceeds of disposition under G.S. 25-9-610 unless the
failure to do so would be commercially unreasonable. A secured party that applies or pays over
for application noncash proceeds shall do so in a commercially reasonable manner.
