the security interest under which a disposition is made secures payment or performance of an
obligation, after making the payments and applications required by subsection (a) of this section
and permitted by subsection (c) of this section:section, both of the following apply:
(1) Unless subdivision (a)(4) of this section requires the secured party to apply or
pay over cash proceeds to a consignor, the secured party shall account to and
pay a debtor for any surplus; andsurplus.
