SECTION 123. G.S. 25-2A-107 reads as rewritten:
"§ 25-2A-107. Waiver or renunciation of claim or right after default.
Any claim or right arising out of an alleged default or breach of warranty may be discharged
in whole or in part without consideration by a written waiver or renunciation in a signed and
record delivered by the aggrieved party."
